    "body": "As the error message says, when you import a dependency you can end up with something that cannot be compiled. For example, you might be using solc 0.8.3 and this contract, and that will compile fine:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0\r\n\r\ncontract Foo {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut if you then import some file that uses `0.8.2` (without the `^`), then the file will not be compilable.\r\n\r\nThat's just an example, the specific reason here depends a lot on what you're doing.\r\n\r\nI'm closing this since I'm pretty sure it's expected behavior. \r\nPlease use [our Discord server](https://hardhat.org/discord) if you have further questions.",
